title: Euro-Med Monitor refutes Israeli account of ‘flour massacre’ in Gaza
description: The Geneva-based Euro-Mediterranean Human Rights Monitor released a report that refutes Israel’s account of the latest “flour massacre” at the Kuwaiti Roundabout where dozens of Palestinian aid seekers were killed, Al Jazeera reported.

title: Embodiment of resilience and Ramadan in Gaza
description: TEHRAN- A week after the start of the Muslim fasting month of Ramadan, Palestinian people in the Gaza Strip are still facing mass starvation caused by Israel’s brutal military onslaught and blockade on the territory.

title: Ansarullah expands anti-Israeli operations to Indian Ocean
description: TEHRAN- Yemeni armed forces have opened a new chapter in operations against Israeli ships as well as U.S. and British ships and warships by expanding their range of fire to the Indian Ocean.

title: A changing world order: The formation of counterhegemonic multipolar order
description: As the Russia-Ukraine crisis and the Gaza invasion become increasingly protracted and complex, there has been a significant shift in the balance of power within the interpretive framework of international order. The differences in perspectives on the world order between the West, particularly the United States, and the Global South are widening.

title: Iran, Syria Defense Ministers meet in Damascus to discuss cooperation
description: TEHRAN – On Saturday, Iranian Defense Minister Brigadier General Mohammad Reza Ashtiani held meetings with his Syrian counterpart Ali Mahmoud Abbas during a visit to Damascus.

title: Iran Air Force safeguards nation with utmost vigilance: commander
description: TEHRAN - Brigadier General Ghader Rahimzadeh, the commander of Khatam al-Anbia Air Defense Base, has underscored the vital role played by the Air Defense Forces in safeguarding the nation's airspace with unwavering vigilance.

title: Rights advocates denounce 'systemic abuse' in Israeli prisons
description: In the shadow of the war raging in Gaza, record numbers of Palestinian detainees are filling Israeli prisons, where they face "systemic abuse" and torture, rights advocates warn, calling for international action, AFP reported.

title: Hezbollah fires missiles at Israeli targets
description: Lebanon’s Hezbollah resistance movement says it has carried out missile attacks against Israel’s Al-Baghdadi site.

title: UN experts raise alarm about anti-Islam sentiment
description: United Nations experts have warned that anti-Islamic sentiment around the world has reached alarming levels.

title: Zakharova: West tried to disrupt Russian presidential election
description: Moscow’s Western opponents actively tried over the past year to disrupt the Russian presidential election, Russia’s Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Maria Zakharova told TASS on Saturday.

title: Israel 'deliberately' targets PRCS ambulances
description: The Palestine Red Crescent Society (PRCS) said 16 of its ambulances had been taken out of service due to Israeli attacks.

title: UAE announces arrival of first aid ship to Gaza
description: The United Arab Emirates (UAE) has announced the arrival of the first ship carrying 200 tons of food and relief supplies to the Gaza Strip, Emirates News Agency (WAM) reported.

title: Gaza ceasefire talks expected to start Sunday
description: Egyptian officials say stalled talks aimed at securing a ceasefire in Gaza between Israel and the Palestinian resistance movement Hamas are expected to restart in earnest in Qatar as soon as Sunday.

title: Belgium PM slams Israel’s ‘inadmissible tactics of starvation’
description: Belgian Prime Minister Alexander De Croo has said Israel’s “tactics of starvation” in Gaza are “inadmissible” as he met UNRWA chief Philippe Lazzarini.

title: Israeli bloodbath: Airstrike kills 36 relatives in Gaza camp
description: Displaced by Israeli bombardment, the Tabatibi family gathered in central Gaza to eat together during the first Friday night of Ramadan, a scene that soon turned into a bloodbath.

title: Hakim: U.S. Making a Big Mistake in Expanding War in Yemen
description: Seyyed Ammar Hakim, the leader of Iraq's National Wisdom Movement, gave a speech on the anniversary of Seyyed Abdul-Aziz Hakim's death in Najaf, stating that Iraq has always stood firmly against those who seek to disturb stability and attack the rights of Iraqi groups.

title: Why is Iran being dragged into the Ukraine war?
description: TEHRAN – The G7 group of countries threatened Iran on Friday saying the country would have to face “new and significant measures” if it decides to give Russia ballistic missiles to be used in the war in Ukraine.

title: Turkish police detain Iranian betting sites head
description: TEHRAN- Turkey has arrested the Iranian ringleader of a betting, gambling and organized crimes site, the Turkish interior minister has announced.

title: Israel’s hopes to disintegrate Iran will not be realized: spox
description: TEHRAN - In a recent development, the spokesman for the Iranian Foreign Ministry has issued a stern condemnation of remarks made by a former Israeli military intelligence officer regarding the potential disintegration of Iran.

title: Separatism in the service of sabotage
description: TEHRAN - In a note, the Iran newspaper addressed the plans of the enemy to divide Iran and said: The enemies of ethnic diversity in Iran, including the British government, have sought to create a crisis, divide the country, and weaken a strong Iran.

title: Constitutional Council confirms 52 Parliamentary Constituencies
description: TEHRAN - Hadi Tahan Nazif, the spokesperson for the Constitutional Council, has announced that the cases of 52 parliamentary constituencies from 11 provinces have undergone scrutiny and have been officially confirmed.

title: Iran calls for global unity at UN to combat escalating Islamophobia
description: TEHRAN - A top Iranian diplomat has issued a plea to the world stage, calling for a united front against the escalating issue of Islamophobia.

title: UNESCO-listed Persepolis to showcase ancient waterways
description: TEHRAN – Unraveling the preparations in light of the upcoming spring holidays, Fars province’s tourism chief announced the reopening of the historic 2-year-500-year-old subterranean waterway of Iran’s Persepolis to holidaymakers, on Saturday.

title: Kashikari: a symbol of ornamental elements in Iran
description: TEHRAN - Kashikari, or tiling, stands as one of the paramount symbols and prominent ornamental elements in Iranian architecture, representing an ancient craft deeply rooted in the land. Initially, tiling predominantly utilized glazed bricks for the structural integrity and aesthetic enhancement of buildings. Over time, however, it transitioned to serve as a defining feature in the appearance and façade of structures.

title: Underground city set to welcome visitors for very first time
description: TEHRAN – As the countdown to welcome Nowruz [Persian new year’s celebration] has started, the ancient underground city of ‘Samen’, situated in Iran’s Malayer, is set to open its doors to the public during the approaching holidays for the very first time.

title: Rare pictorial carpets put on show at Tehran museum
description: TEHRAN – On Saturday, the Carpet Museum of Iran opened its doors to a captivating exhibition titled “Pictorial Carpets: A Study of Qajar-Era Rugs” in celebration of the approaching Nowruz holiday.

title: Mongolia to join UNESCO's Nowruz dossier
description: TEHRAN – Mongolia has voiced its interest in joining the Persian New Year (Nowruz) dossier, a multinational intangible cultural heritage registered with the UN Educational, Scientific, and Cultural Organization.

title: Abdollah Veisi new head coach of Foolad: PGPL
description: TEHRAN – Abdollah Veisi took charge of Iranian top-flight football club Foolad in 2023/24 Iran Persian Gulf Professional League (PGPL) on Saturday.

title: “For the Sake of Ava” on screen at Spanish festival
description: TEHRAN-Iranian director’s film “For the Sake of Ava” is competing at the 4th edition of the Festival Internacional de Cine Independiente de Madrid (FICIMAD), which is currently underway in the Spanish capital.

title: Iranian director to stage musical play on Rustam and Sohrab
description: TEHRAN- Iranian director Hossein Parsai is set to bring to life the legendary tale of Rustam and Sohrab from the Shahnameh, the epic masterpiece of the Persian poet Ferdowsi, in a musical play

title: Sadegh Tabrizi’s untitled painting sold at Christie's
description: TEHRAN-An untitled painting by Iranian artist Sadegh Tabrizi was sold at the Christie's Paris auction “Collections – The Online Sale” held from February 29 to March 13.

title: Iranian Personal Injury Lawyers & Seeking Justice
description: IranianLawyer.com - Iranian Personal Injury Lawyers serve as advocates for individuals who have suffered injuries due to the negligence or wrongdoing of others.

title: Iranian Litigation Lawyers’ Role in Contract Litigation Cases
description: IranianAttorney.biz - Contract litigation arises when parties to a contractual agreement are in dispute over the terms, performance, or other aspects of the contract. In these situations, litigation lawyers play a crucial role in representing their clients' interests and navigating the legal process.

title: Leader allocates money to help free prisoners
description: TEHRAN - Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, the Leader of the Islamic Revolution, has earmarked 20 billion rials (some $40,000) for releasing prisoners of unintentional crimes.

title: Iran ranks among nations with High Development Index
description: TEHRAN –According to the 2023/24 Human Development Report (HDR) by the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), Iran has been placed among the countries with a High Development Index (HDI).

title: ‘Effective implementation of intl. drug control conventions is essential’
description: TEHRAN –The secretary general of the anti-narcotics headquarters has stressed the need for effective implementation of anti-narcotics programs in the region free from political considerations.

title: WHO official calls Iran’s family physician program ‘valuable’
description: TEHRAN – The World Health Organization (WHO) regional director for Europe has referred to Iran’s family physician program as a valuable plan, calling member states to share experiences in this regard.

title: Humanitarian situation in Gaza is ‘beyond catastrophic’
description: Jagan Chapagain, the head of the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies, says civilians in Gaza are “facing an unprecedented level of indignity, misery and suffering”.

title: TEDPIX falls over 1,500 points on Saturday
description: TEHRAN - TEDPIX, the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE), fell 1,517 points (0.07 percent) to 2,148,518 on Saturday, which is the first day of the Iranian calendar week.

title: World’s journalists visit industrial zones in Beijing
description: BEIJING- China International Press Communication Center (CIPCC) arranged a program for journalists from around the world to visit a number of industrial zones in capital Beijing on Friday.

title: Iran’s GDP growth stands at 4.5% in 9 months: CBI
description: TEHRAN- Iran's gross domestic product (GDP) including oil grew 4.5 percent in the first nine months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21-December 21, 2023), compared to the first three quarters of last year, according to the Central Bank of Iran (CBI).

title: Iran, Azerbaijan discuss co-op in water, electricity industries
description: TEHRAN - Energy officials from Iran and the Republic of Azerbaijan emphasized the need to strengthen cooperation in the fields of water and electricity.

title: Tehran, Kabul sign MOU on agricultural cooperation
description: TEHRAN - Officials from Iran and the government of Afghanistan signed a memorandum of understanding (MOU) for cooperation in agricultural sectors.

title: Israeli military faces biggest mental health crisis since 1973 war: army official
description: Thousands of Israeli soldiers are suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder or other combat trauma, according to the head of the army’s mental health department.

title: Annual petrochemical exports to hit 29m tons: NPC head
description: TEHRAN – The head of Iran’s National Petrochemical Company (NPC) has said the country’s petrochemical exports are expected to reach 29 million tons by the end of the current Iranian calendar year (March 19).

title: Salimi earns Iran’s fourth quota in taekwondo for Paris
description: TEHRAN – Iranian taekwondo athlete Arian Salimi secured a berth in the 2024 Olympic Games in Paris.

title: Milad Taghavi elected head of Iran volleyball federation
description: TEHRAN – Milad Taghavi was elected as president of Iran Volleyball Federation on Saturday for a four-year term till 2028.
